{
  "texts": [
    "One or more Laplacian smoothing iterations are run to improve the mesh quality.",
    "Lastly, the mesh vertices of the coarse mesh are snapped to the closest vertices of the original mesh.",
    "The snapping avoids the need for more sophisticated interpolation methods to map the field data between the meshes.",
    "The new mesh is static (invariant in time).",
    "While demonstrating the potential of mesh reduction based on flow physics, the original S 3 algorithm has the following shortcomings:• Point cloud reduction: selecting points based on high metric values, e.g., the temporal variance of a field, leads to large empty regions in some parts of the domain, while most points are clustered in other parts."
  ]
}